---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ASCIIBrackets from '../components/ASCIIBrackets.astro';

// Define bracket types for showcase
const bracketTypes = [
  { type: 'js-object', color: 'yellow', label: 'app.js', title: 'JavaScript Object', content: 'JavaScript-styled brackets for web security articles' },
  { type: 'html', color: 'blue', label: 'index.html', title: 'HTML Tags', content: 'HTML-styled brackets for frontend security topics' },
  { type: 'jsx', color: 'cyan', label: 'Component.jsx', title: 'React/JSX', content: 'React component style for modern web app security' },
  { type: 'css', color: 'purple', label: 'styles.css', title: 'CSS Rules', content: 'CSS-styled brackets for UI/UX security considerations' },
  { type: 'python', color: 'green', label: 'security.py', title: 'Python Function', content: 'Python-styled brackets for security automation articles' },
  { type: 'markdown', color: 'teal', label: 'README.md', title: 'Markdown', content: 'Markdown-styled brackets for documentation and policy guides' },
  { type: 'sql', color: 'orange', label: 'query.sql', title: 'SQL Query', content: 'SQL-styled brackets for database security topics' },
  { type: 'bash', color: 'red', label: 'script.sh', title: 'Bash Script', content: 'Bash-styled brackets for system hardening guides' },
  
  // Security brackets
  { type: 'security-report', color: 'violet', label: 'REPORT', title: 'Security Report', content: 'Formal security assessment report format' },
  { type: 'code-review', color: 'teal', label: 'REVIEW', title: 'Code Review', content: 'Security-focused code review documentation' },
  { type: 'vulnerability', color: 'red', label: 'CVE-2025', title: 'Vulnerability', content: 'Critical vulnerability documentation and resolution' },
  
  // Classic brackets for comparison
  { type: 'square', color: 'blue', label: 'classic', title: 'Square Brackets', content: 'Traditional square brackets [ ]' },
  { type: 'curly', color: 'green', label: 'classic', title: 'Curly Braces', content: 'Traditional curly braces { }' },
  { type: 'angle', color: 'yellow', label: 'classic', title: 'Angle Brackets', content: 'Traditional angle brackets < >' },
  { type: 'pipe', color: 'red', label: 'classic', title: 'Pipes', content: 'Traditional pipe brackets | |' }
];
---

<Layout>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-container">
      <h1>ASCII Bracket Showcase</h1>
      <p>
        Explore our various programming-inspired bracket styles for blog posts and content sections.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="blog-container">
    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Programming-Style Brackets</h2>
      <p>These bracket styles are used to theme our blog posts based on their technical content. Each style represents a different programming language or technology.</p>
      
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0;">
        {bracketTypes.slice(0, 8).map(bracket => (
          <ASCIIBrackets type={bracket.type} color={bracket.color} label={bracket.label}>
            <div style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center;">
              <h4 style={`color: var(--${bracket.color}); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;`}>{bracket.title}</h4>
              <p>{bracket.content}</p>
            </div>
          </ASCIIBrackets>
        ))}
      </div>
      
      <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-top: 3rem;">Security-Focused Brackets</h2>
      <p>These bracket styles are specifically designed for security documentation and reporting.</p>
      
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0;">
        {bracketTypes.slice(8, 11).map(bracket => (
          <ASCIIBrackets type={bracket.type} color={bracket.color} label={bracket.label}>
            <div style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center;">
              <h4 style={`color: var(--${bracket.color}); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;`}>{bracket.title}</h4>
              <p>{bracket.content}</p>
            </div>
          </ASCIIBrackets>
        ))}
      </div>
      
      <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-top: 3rem;">Classic Bracket Styles</h2>
      <p>These are the traditional bracket styles that are also available for use.</p>
      
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0;">
        {bracketTypes.slice(11).map(bracket => (
          <ASCIIBrackets type={bracket.type} color={bracket.color}>
            <div style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center;">
              <h4 style={`color: var(--${bracket.color}); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;`}>{bracket.title}</h4>
              <p>{bracket.content}</p>
            </div>
          </ASCIIBrackets>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Using Brackets in Blog Posts</h2>
      
      <ASCIIBrackets type="markdown" color="violet" label="howto.md">
        <div style="padding: 1rem;">
          <p>When creating a new blog post, specify the bracket style in the frontmatter:</p>
          
          <pre style="background: rgba(7,54,66,0.1); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; overflow-x: auto; margin: 1rem 0;">
---
title: "My Technical Article"
// ... other frontmatter
bracketType: "python" 
bracketColor: "green"
bracketLabel: "security_script.py"
---</pre>
          
          <p>Available bracket types:</p>
          <ul style="columns: 2; margin: 1rem 0; list-style-type: none;">
            <li><code>js-object</code> - JavaScript object</li>
            <li><code>html</code> - HTML tags</li>
            <li><code>jsx</code> - React/JSX component</li>
            <li><code>css</code> - CSS rule</li>
            <li><code>python</code> - Python function</li>
            <li><code>markdown</code> - Markdown</li>
            <li><code>sql</code> - SQL query</li>
            <li><code>bash</code> - Bash script</li>
            <li><code>square</code> - Square brackets</li>
            <li><code>curly</code> - Curly braces</li>
            <li><code>angle</code> - Angle brackets</li>
            <li><code>pipe</code> - Pipes</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </ASCIIBrackets>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
